{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"A complete end-to-end example using Cambium to parse, traverse, edit,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and evaluate a small arithmetic language.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Calculator sample is a standalone SwiftPM package that exercises"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Cambium’s full public surface against a real grammar. It ships as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"library ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorCore"},{"type":"text","text":") plus an interactive REPL ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"calc-repl"},{"type":"text","text":") so the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same pieces can be unit-tested and poked at by hand."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For a step-by-step walkthrough that builds the calculator one","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Cambium subsystem at a time, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tutorials use the same source files documented here as their","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"canonical implementation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Tip","type":"aside","style":"tip"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The grammar covers integer and real literals, parenthesized"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sub-expressions, unary minus, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"round(expr)"},{"type":"text","text":" built-in, and the four"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"arithmetic operators with normal precedence. The parser preserves input"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text losslessly, recovers from malformed input by emitting missing and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error nodes, and only evaluates trees with no parse diagnostics."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"What-it-covers","text":"What it covers","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The sample is organized to demonstrate one Cambium concept per source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file, so each topic in the Cambium documentation has a concrete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"counterpart you can read, build, and modify."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Defining a language.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorLanguage.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" derives a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance from a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UInt32"},{"type":"text","text":"-backed enum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@CambiumSyntaxKind"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StaticText"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Lexing.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorLexer.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" produces tokens with byte offsets"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the parser to feed into a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Recursive-descent CST construction.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorParser.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uses checkpoints ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/checkpoint()"},{"type":"text","text":" \/"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/startNode(at:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":") for left-associative"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operator precedence, and emits missing\/error nodes for recovery."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"A typed AST overlay.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorTypedAST.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" defines one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumASTSupport\/TypedSyntaxNode"},{"type":"text","text":" per AST shape and exposes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"kind-specific accessors over the generic CST."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Borrowed traversal.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorEvaluator.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" walks the typed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"AST through borrowed cursors with no per-node allocation."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Owned handles.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorParseResult.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" materializes long-lived"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTokenHandle"},{"type":"text","text":" arrays"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":nodes"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":tokens"},{"type":"text","text":" REPL commands."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Incremental reparse.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorParser.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" consults a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ReuseOracle"},{"type":"text","text":" to splice unchanged subtrees from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"previous tree; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorSession.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" builds a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness"},{"type":"text","text":" and forwards cached evaluator entries"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"across edits."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Replacement and witnesses.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorFold.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" constant-folds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"one node at a time using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SharedSyntaxTree.replacing(_:with:context:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and classifies references through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Analysis sidecars.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorSession.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" keeps an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/ExternalAnalysisCache"},{"type":"text","text":" of evaluated values and a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/SyntaxMetadataStore"},{"type":"text","text":" of per-evaluation metadata."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Serialization.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorSession.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" round-trips the current"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tree through "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumSerialization\/GreenSnapshotDecoder"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"serializeGreenSnapshot()"},{"type":"text","text":" for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":save"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":load"},{"type":"text","text":" commands."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sharing across tasks.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorParallelEvaluator.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" uses a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":" with a structured-concurrent fork\/join"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"evaluator that shares an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/ExternalAnalysisCache"},{"type":"text","text":" and a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/SyntaxMetadataStore"},{"type":"text","text":" across tasks."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Parallel parsing.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalculatorParallelParser.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" shows a parser"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variant that splits work across child tasks while preserving the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same lossless CST output."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Running-it","text":"Ru